About me
Hey, I’m an independent web & software developer from Vilnius, Lithuania. Check out my projects and contact me at pijusv92@gmail.com  if you have any inquiries.
You can also find me here  
 

 
What I do:
Front-end

React, Redux, ES6, Javascript, HTML, CSS3

Back-end

NodeJS, PHP, APIs, Jekyll, Webpack, Docker

Databases

Mongodb, Postgresql, Redis

CMS

Wordpress, Jekyll with Prose.io

Cloud

AWS: EC2, ECS, S3, RDS

Projects/Developed/Static Websites/amade.title: amadea.lt
Projects/Developed/Static Websites/amade.body:
Amadea

Development Stack: Jekyll, Bootstrap
Design
Client required a simple website that lists all their services with prices and descriptions.
There was a bit of a challenge when thinking about how to structure the content. While researching websites from the same category it seemed like most chose to list their services like an e-shop and the resulting websites felt overwhelming because of the huge amounts of information and difficulty moving from one service and its description to other.
My main goal was ease of use and I decided to use nested tabs. First, together with the client we restructured the services into branching categories to display the information in smaller chunks. It shows the user only relevant information and by having the descriptions in a tab next to prices, user can easily navigate around without losing their track in the list.
